Abusing the power of graphics

Abusing the power of graphics

Effective display of data

  • Generate graphics effectively
    • consistency of plots
    • avoid common mistakes
  • Create informative plots
    • starts with a simple display
    • extension of a graphics without changing much
    • complex graphics to be generated in less effort
    • displays data in several level of details
  • Grammar of graphics help us achieve the goal

Grammar of graphics

  • Leland Wilkinson (1999)
    • grammar of graphics
  • Hadley Wickham (2005)
    • continued working with the grammar
    • implemented in R:
    • layered grammar of graphics (2010)
  • R packages we will use in this lecture
  install.packages(c("ggplot2", "ggmap", "gapminder", "reshape2"))

How the grammar works

Example: ggplot

ggplot(data=mtcars, aes(x = disp, y = mpg, color = factor(cyl))) + 
  geom_point()

Example: ggplot

ggplot(data = mtcars, aes(x = disp, y = mpg, color = factor(cyl))) + 
  geom_point() + geom_smooth(method="lm")

Case study: exploratory visualization

library(gapminder)
dat <- subset(gapminder, year == 2007)
q <- ggplot(data = dat, aes(x = log(gdpPercap), y = lifeExp))
q + geom_point()

Case study: exploratory visualization

q + geom_point(aes(size = sqrt(pop/pi)), pch = 21, show.legend = FALSE) +
   scale_size_continuous(range=c(1,30))

Case study: exploratory visualization

q + geom_point(aes(size = sqrt(pop/pi)), pch = 21, show.legend = FALSE) +
   scale_size_continuous(range=c(1,30)) + aes(fill = continent)

Case study: exploratory visualization

q + geom_point(aes(size = sqrt(pop/pi)), pch = 21, show.legend = FALSE) +
   scale_size_continuous(range=c(1,30)) + aes(fill = continent, alpha=0.3)

Faceting in display

library(reshape2)
ggplot(tips, aes(size, tip, color=sex)) + geom_point() +
  geom_smooth(method="lm", se=FALSE) + facet_grid(smoker~time)

Display of spatial data

pdat <- read.csv("tempdat.csv")
ggplot(pdat, aes(x=long, y=lat,group=group)) + 
  geom_polygon(aes(fill=temp), colour = alpha("white", 1/2), size = 0.2) + theme_bw() + 
  theme(legend.position = "none", text = element_blank(), line = element_blank()) + 
  scale_fill_continuous(low="blue", high="hotpink")

Display data on google maps

library(ggmap)
crimes <- read.csv("omaha-crimes.csv")
omaps <- get_map(location = 'Omaha', source = 'stamen', maptype = 'toner')
ggmap(omaps) +
  geom_point(size=5, alpha = 1/2, aes(lon,lat, color=type), data = crimes)

Display data on google maps

crimes <- read.csv("omaha-crimes.csv")
omaps <- get_map(location = 'Omaha', maptype = 'roadmap', zoom = 11, color='bw')
ggmap(omaps) +
  geom_point(size=5, alpha = 1/2, aes(lon,lat, color=type), data = crimes)
